Text.Value: I'm sick with a deep malaise, one that came from a place beyond the stars.
I've broken out in weird, singing hives - a sure sign of faerie infection.
I've picked up a diabolic disease - the symptoms are quite hellish.
Poor dear. Poor, poor dear. Who did this to you?
Sisters! Protect the patients!
The doctor is absent today. Come back another time.
Down to the theatre, be swift, be saved.
Join the line - you will be seen.
No thanks, I'll take my chances out there.
ROAR AT THIS INJUSTICE.
Yes yes, but all must wait. The doctor's hands are full.
Quiet! Quiet! Everyone must wait their turn, wait in line... Doctor's orders.
Get away from me!
Mimic the symptoms of Assassin's Blood, a well-known poison.
I'm not a patient - I've been hired as a new healer.
I am but a nurse here, the Surgeon... he will be able to examine you in full.
My dear lady - look at my complexion. I am at death's door.
Enough of this - I'm going in.
Such cruelty, such callousness. And in our time of need. Away.
Feign the symptoms of a disease most terrible.
My mind is full of holes, and some of them are still being punched.
The unseen wounds of war - the doctor's hand will close them.
The doctor will see you. The doctor will soothe.
You endanger the sick!

EditorData.AnimationTags: Performance Check FAIL: player attempts to feign illness, but is not very convincing {CodyM}
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Disgusted reaction to player's pretend illness.

Text.Value: Plague! Pest! In line, or leave.
The doctor will see you now.
What is the primary symptom?
I'm only truly happy when I'm ending someone's life.
Poor creature - so sad, so sick.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Performance Check PASS: player successfully feigns being extremely ill. {CodyM}

Text.Value: Pretend to be ill.
Join the line - you will be seen.
Down the corridor. Down to theatre you go.
Every monster you can imagine, man or beast, has tried to kill me. I should really see the doctor.
Hrm, hrm. Let me check, let me check.
Not sick, not welcome!
Not so well. But well enough to wait. Join the line, and you will be seen.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The nurse 'looks' you over, assessing your condition.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Upon investigation, deduces that you're not that sick.

Text.Value: I am no patient - I've been hired as a spiritual advisor.
Let me examine your skull.
What in the Hells can you see?
Everything. I lose control of myself, and kill without command.
The Surgeon will be most interested in you.
Be patient, be well.
As pale as a ghost. You must see the doctor immediately.

EditorData.NodeContext: shocked reaction -the patient is pale as a ghost

Text.Value: Fine fine. I'll get in line.
Wait! My wounds may not be visible on the outside, but I still need help.
There is no shame in an end. All things come to be lost. But if you wish to be examined...
Poorly, quite poorly indeed...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The nurse 'looks' you over, assessing your condition.

Text.Value: Fine, fine. I'll get back in line.
You're not sick, not sick at all. Wait in line.
You can let me in or I can burn, electrify, or freeze this place - maybe even all three. Your choice.
Too many thoughts - a thrice-cursed ailment. The emptiness you yearn for will be yours again.
I'm sick as a dog - dark compulsions addle my mind.
I'm no patient, your surgeon heard I have the steadiest hand this side of Faern.
I'm not a patient - I'm the doctor's new assistant.
Pestilence! Pestilence and sin!
No worse, no better, no need to be here.
Here to see the doctor? Are we poorly? Are we desperately poorly?
An answer to our prayers!
A most impatient patient... Very well. Still your cries, restless soul.
*There's a hint of recognition in her eyes as she studies you.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The receptionist recognises that you're referring to your mental health.

Text.Value: A unique disease - one which has never passed through this institution before.
I am no patient - I've just been hired as an expert in maladaptive necromantic malaise.
When I try to sleep I am plagued by distressing sights.
I don't have time to wait - I need to see the doctor right now.
Leave.

Synopsis: Receptionist at the entrance of the Hospital. She's mostly supposed to be there for flavor and to provide directions to the operating room (down the hallway and under the observation area.) If you piss her off or try to circumvent her to see the doctor, she'll fight you.
